Join us in Todos Santos!

Please join us for our computational biology and next-generation sequencing workshop at the CSU Center in Todos Santos, Mexico. Here is a summary of the topics that we are looking forward to covering over the course of the week.




Computational Workshop

Monday May 4: Introduction to high-throughput sequencing and computational biology

  • 08:00-08:45 Breakfast
  • 09:00-10:30 Introduction to Todos Santos and Group Discussion
  • 10:30-11:00 High-Throughput Sequencing Technologies
  • 11:00-12:00 UNIX and Command Line Tools
  • 12:00-13:00 Lunch
  • 13:00-16:00 Manipulating and Obtaining Genomics Data
  • 16:00-17:30 Alignment and Read Mapping

Tuesday May 5: RNA-seq

  • 08:00-08:45 Breakfast
  • 09:00-12:00 RNA-seq Data Analysis I
  • 12:00-13:00 Lunch
  • 13:00-17:00 RNA-seq Data Analysis II
  • 17:00-18:30 Research Presentations (with Refreshments)

Wednesday May 6: Comparative genomic analysis and data visualization

  • 08:00-08:45 Breakfast
  • 09:00-10:30 Assembly and Annotation
  • 10:30-12:00 Variant Calling
  • 12:00-13:00 Lunch
  • 13:00-14:30 Introduction to R, R Markdown, and Data Visualization
  • 14:30-15:15 Plotting Genomic Data with R and ggplot
  • 15:15-16:00 Figure Drawing in R
  • 16:00-17:00 Circular Representations of Genomic Data with Circos
  • 18:00-20:00 Workshop Dinner and Celebration

Thursday May 7: Scripting and GitHub

  • 08:00-08:45 Breakfast
  • 09:00-10:00 Code Management (GitHub)
  • 10:00-12:00 Bash Scripting
  • 12:00-13:00 Lunch
  • 13:00-17:00 Python Scripting



Optional Wet-Lab Extension on NGS Library Construction

Friday May 8: Illumina Library Construction and 16S Sequencing

  • 08:00-08:45 Breakfast
  • 09:00-09:45 Illumina sequencing chemistry and adapters
  • 09:45-10:30 DNA/RNA quality control: methods for estimation of nucleic acid concentration, purity and integrity
  • 10:30-10:45 Introduction to 16S rRNA microbiome profiling
  • 10:45-12:00 Wet-lab: Illumina 16S rRNA amplicon library construction
  • 12:00-13:00 Lunch
  • 13:00-13:30 Illumina Library quality control: Quantification
  • 13:30-14:00 Illumina Library quality control: Size selection
  • 14:00-15:30 Wet Lab: Magnetic bead cleanup and Illumina 16S amplicon library gel electrophoresis
  • 15:30-16:00 Barcoding and multiplexing techniques
  • 16:00-16:30 Fragmentation methods

Saturday May 9: Long-Read Sequencing and Oxford MinIon Run

  • 08:00-08:45 Breakfast
  • 09:00-10:00 Introduction to long-read DNA sequencing technologies
  • 10:00-12:00 Wet-lab: Construction of Oxford Nanopore libraries and sequencing on a MinIon
  • 12:00-13:00 Lunch
  • 13:00-14:00 Experimental design in high-throughput sequencing projects
  • 14:00-15:00 Making choices in high-throughput sequencing projects
  • 15:00-16:00 Results from Oxford Nanopore sequencing run
